# Finalize and Move Update Set
Open Update sets that you have created recently
Change the State from In Progress to Complete.
Click on Update
Click on ‘Export to XML’
Download the File

Testing the Update Set 
Open another instance to test the update set
Open another instance and search for Retrieve Update sets
Click on ‘Export Update Set from XML’.
Select the file that you have downloaded in the previous instance
Click on Upload
After uploading you can see the New Record 
Open that record and see the data
Click on Preview Update Set
Click on Commit Update Set to transfer the whole data 
Now you can see all the data was transferred 
Validate that no elements are missing.

# Data Integrity

Description
Field Validation and Automation
  Mandatory Field Enforcement :Software-related details such as Software Name, Version, and Business Justification were made mandatory.
This validation happened at both the client side (UI Policies) and the server side (Business Rules), preventing incomplete submissions.
 Automatic Population of Values: To reduce manual effort, certain fields were auto-filled.
For example, the Requested For field defaulted to the logged-in user, while Department and Location values were pulled dynamically from the user’s profile.
 Testing & Validation:End-to-end testing confirmed that requests followed the correct lifecycle: submission → approvals → catalog task assignment → fulfillment → closure. 
Notifications and logs were verified to ensure accuracy at every step.
Data Reliability:These measures helped maintain integrity across all related tables — Request (REQ), Requested Item (RITM), and Catalog Task (SCTASK).
Each layer was validated to prevent unauthorized or incomplete requests.
